    <title>1828 Apr. 4, Lebanon [to] Mr. Fergusson / T. C. Anderson</title>
  </titleInfo>
  <abstract>This is a letter from T. C. Anderson to A. Fergusson, dated April 4, 1828. Anderson is informing Fergusson that his son, William, received an admonition from his school's faculty. He was found guilty of spreading false and slanderous rumors. Anderson counciled Fergusson to give William parental advice when he returns home.</abstract>
